key_events: User requested to test the register endpoint by creating a user using CURL.
Compilation errors were identified in cmd/api/main.go related to undefined rate limiters.
Rate limiters were properly initialized in the NewService function in auth.go.
A syntax error was discovered at the beginning of auth.go, preventing the server from starting.
The syntax error in auth.go was resolved by removing unexpected characters.
The server was successfully started after fixing the syntax error.
The register endpoint was tested using CURL, revealing that the username 'testuser' already exists.
The register endpoint correctly checks for existing usernames, but prevented the creation of a new user as intended.
Further testing with a unique username is needed to verify full functionality of the register endpoint.
